<br>
Kilal Riverrunner<br>
The Nameless <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ukilalriverrunner.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kilal Riverrunner</A> at: 6/27/01 10:53:01 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/urumil.showPublicProfile?language=EN>rumil</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(6/27/01 1:17:27 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.e-corridor.com/images/EQ/tinyrumil.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Kiting Snow Cougars...</span><hr size=1> Keep snaring them till it sticks, pull them to a water edge or 'quiet' spot, then fear and dot them, reapply fear as it fades, same for dot.<br>
<br>
since the zone is roughly 30 and up, it will become easier as you get higher in level. <p>Warden of Tunare<br>
Wanderer of the 52nd Ring<br>
Innoruuk Server<br>
"Just once or twice its good for your Soul." ~ Oingo Boingo
<br><img src="http://www.ecorridor.com/images/EQ/deathpoketext.jpg"></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ugallatin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Gallatin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(6/28/01 8:40:15 am)</font><br>     <br>Community Supporter<br> <BR><img src=http://astro.temple.edu/~fmoffat/img/small.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Kiting Snow Cougars...</span><hr size=1> At level 30, Immolate is still going to get resisted quite a bit. It's a PITA, drove me crazy until around 33, I guess. <br>
<br>
You didn't mention using the Panic Animal line of spells. Are you fearing them, or just trying traditional kiting?<br>
<br>
Cougars are a decent fight with Drones and regen at 34, so it's not going to be a simple fight for you at 30. Good exp, tho. And a druid is a big help in a group over there. Find a tank and another healer, and you're golden. Thorns on the tank, snare and SoW, and the exp will fly. <p><b>Gallatin</b><p>
<font size=3>Everyone is entitled to their own wrong opinion</font></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uknottyrootfist.showPublicProfile?language=EN>KnottyRootfist</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(12/1/01 6:03:52 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Kiting Snow Cougars...</span><hr size=1>  I have been hunting the Snow cougars with my husband who is a rogue. The best way we have found is to ensnare them and then Terrorize.  We Take very little damage although I sometimes have to terrorize more than once.  So Far it is working Great.<br>
<br>
Ferne <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/userberus00.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Serberus00</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(12/1/01 12:11:04 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Kiting Snow Cougars...</span><hr size=1> I came here at level 25 and was able to kill a yellow cougar but I kept going OOM (115 wis, just leather + tarnished scimitar, woo).<br>
<br>
Came back at 26 and it was much easier, just make sure you only pull yellows, you won't take reds.<br>
<br>
Pull with say Burst of Flame and pull them past the gnomes until you reach a large stretch of land.<br>
<br>
Snare until it sticks.<br>
<br>
Fear until it sticks.<br>
<br>
Creeping Crud them and just med, they'll just slowly wander towards the sea, and your too far away to pull adds. If you get trained, its someone elses fault - blame them =)<br>
<br>
fear and re-dot as required, takes about 10 minutes per cat at sub 34 but its safe and steady experience, can do cougars till level 40 (quadding from 34).<br>
<br>
Serberus <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ulaeryn01.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Laeryn01</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(12/2/01 6:23:43 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Kiting Snow Cougars...</span><hr size=1> I haven't used this trick for quite a while, so I'm not sure if it still works. But, if you pull the cougars to the dock (Make sure you're not in wolf form) and fear them there, there is a nice little pathing bug. Snare, fear, and dot, then, with a fast-casting nuke hit him every time you want him to turn around. Can get annoying if he runs into the ocean, however. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ugippah.showPublicProfile?language=EN>gippah</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_star.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(12/13/01 3:23:48 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://destroy.austin.tx.us/diary/cgi-bin/random.cgi WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Kiting Snow Cougars...</span><hr size=1> Soloing cougars here is a real challenge.  If you're of the appropriate level to get good exp off of them, they'll resist a lot more than they should and you're likely to get an add or two every other battle.<br>
<br>
As inviting as dicing up these animals is, it's not really worth it IMHO.  Same with Stonebrunt.  VI obviously thought long and hard about not allowing Druids to take advantage of these zones.  =)<br>
<br>
If you really want to fight in Velious, just invis yourself and walk over to GD and play with some Tizmaks.  They'll give you nice experience up until 35, and they're very very simple to kill. <p><br>
<hr width=20%>
