</font></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/upatofnaud.showPublicProfile?language=EN>patofnaud</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(12/14/01 6:28:18 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Kiting Snow Cougars...</span><hr size=1> /shrug<br>
<br>
I quad'ed Cougars over by ToFS all through 38 and 39 and experience rocked. Plus, I snagged about 6 earrings and 4 HQ Pelts. At 40, they went light blue on me.<br>
<br>
It's like anything, when you are fighting at the dock, I would assume your probably low 30's, at the level most anything you run into will start to be hard like that. You may want to just try snare/root/DoT and med for a bit and get a level or two more on them. <p><body lang=EN-US style='tab-interval:.5in'>

